Title: Reading a Text File from GitHub Repository in Google Colab using Python
 Objective

To read a text file stored in a GitHub repository directly into a Python program using Google Colab.

 Concept:- 

GitHub files are normally accessed using a URL, but raw files cannot be directly read using standard file handling methods unless converted into a raw format link.

Google Colab allows fetching such files using:

requests module
urllib module
Direct file reading via raw URL

Requirements:- 
Google Colab environment
Internet connection
GitHub repository file link

Step 1: Get Raw File URL from GitHub
Open your file on GitHub
Click on "Raw" button
Copy the URL

Example:

https://raw.githubusercontent.com/username/repo/main/file1.txt
Step 2: Python Code (Method 1 – Using requests)
import requests

# Raw file URL
url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/username/repo/main/file1.txt"

# Send request to fetch file
response = requests.get(url)

# Check if request successful
if response.status_code == 200:
    data = response.text
    print("File Content:\n")
    print(data)
else:
    print("Failed to retrieve file")

Step 3: Python Code (Method 2 – Using urllib)
import urllib.request

url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/username/repo/main/file1.txt"

# Open URL and read data
file = urllib.request.urlopen(url)

content = file.read().decode('utf-8')

print("File Content:\n")
print(content)

Step 4: Save File Locally in Colab (Optional)
with open("downloaded_file.txt", "w") as f:
    f.write(content)

print("File saved successfully")

Explanation of Logic
Convert GitHub file → Raw URL
Send request to server
Fetch file content as text
Decode (if needed)
Print or store locally
